sub_title: User Experience Designer | Master's in Human-Computer Interaction | CEMS Master's in International Management
summary:
I am a multidisciplinary user experience designer who is interested more in understanding the problem and the users, rather than moving pixels around right away. That's why you can hear more questions than answers from me - especially at the first steps. 

I believe that having diverse background and skillset makes me a better designer as it allows me to see the problems from different lenses and enrich the team's capabilities.

In the last five years, I lived in 6 different countries on 3 different continents, worked in different types of organizations, and constantly made sure I kept learning something new. It wouldn't be wrong if I say I can adapt to changes quickly - and frankly - I love the changes and new experiences.

If you have something to tell or ask, feel free to message me. I enjoy the exchange of ideas and experiences.
